<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-08T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-08T05:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">865.4016/60: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-08T11:00:00+01:00">September 8, 1938—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 8—8:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>228. My telegram No. 187, July 29, noon and my telegram No. 207,
                                August 19, 6 p.m. We have informally requested information
                                concerning various aspects of recent anti-Semitic decrees as
                                applicable to American citizens but have thus far succeeded only in
                                obtaining confirmation of assurances reported in my No. 207, August
                                19.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>